ðŸ”¹ What this project does (Simple words)
Creates Linux users
Creates groups
Adds users to groups
Sets file & directory permissions
Assigns ownership
ðŸ‘‰ Used daily by DevOps / SysAdmins to manage access securely.


#!/bin/bash

# -----------------------------
# User & Permission Management Script
# -----------------------------
# This script:
# 1. Creates a group
# 2. Creates users
# 3. Adds users to the group
# 4. Sets directory permissions

# Run this script as ROOT user

# --------- Variables ---------
GROUP_NAME=devteam
USERS=("user1" "user2" "user3")
DIR_PATH=/opt/dev_project

# --------- Create Group ---------
if ! getent group $GROUP_NAME > /dev/null; then
    groupadd $GROUP_NAME
    echo "Group $GROUP_NAME created"
else
    echo "Group $GROUP_NAME already exists"
fi

# --------- Create Users and Assign Group ---------
for USER in "${USERS[@]}"
do
    if ! id $USER &>/dev/null; then
        useradd -m -g $GROUP_NAME $USER
        echo "User $USER created and added to group $GROUP_NAME"
    else
        echo "User $USER already exists"
    fi
done

# --------- Create Directory ---------
mkdir -p $DIR_PATH

# --------- Set Ownership ---------
chown -R :$GROUP_NAME $DIR_PATH

# --------- Set Permissions ---------
chmod -R 770 $DIR_PATH

echo "User and permission setup completed successfully"

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Variables Section: GROUP_NAME=devteam
USERS=("user1" "user2" "user3")
DIR_PATH=/opt/dev_project
âœ” List of users
âœ” Directory to secure

2) groupadd devteam: ðŸ‘‰ Creates a Linux group
Used to manage permissions centrally

3) Create Users: useradd -m -g devteam user1
| Option | Meaning               |
| ------ | --------------------- |
| `-m`   | Create home directory |
| `-g`   | Primary group         |


4) Loop Explanation: for USER in "${USERS[@]}"
ðŸ‘‰ Loops through multiple users
âœ” Automation
âœ” No repeated commands


5) Create Project Directory: mkdir -p /opt/dev_project
Application folder
Shared workspace


6) Set Ownership:
chown -R :devteam /opt/dev_project
âœ” Group owns the directory
âœ” All users in group can access

7) Set Permissions:
| Permission | Meaning            |
| ---------- | ------------------ |
| 7          | Owner: full access |
| 7          | Group: full access |
| 0          | Others: no access  |


8) chmod +x user_management.sh
9) sudo ./user_management.sh:User creation requires root access












